  "reference_number": "RUS0258",
  "remarks": "\nAs Chief of the General Staff of the Armed Forces and First Deputy Minister of Defence, Major General Victor Gulevich is an active, visible and senior military leader in Belarus and, as part of the top-level chain of command, is responsible for directing the actions of the Belarusian armed forces, which have supported and enabled the Russian invasion of Ukraine. The Belarusian armed forces have conducted joint military exercises with Russian armed forces, and also consented to the deployment of Russian troops along the border of Belarus with Ukraine, which has directly contributed to Russia’s ability to both threaten and attack Ukraine, including from positions in Belarus. Gulevich therefore is or has been involved in destabilising Ukraine and undermining or threatening the territorial integrity, sovereignty and independence of Ukraine. \n The trust services sanctions were imposed on 21/03/2023.",
